Former Aviation Minister, Chief Femi Fani-Kayode said he has  not left the Peoples Democratic Party, PDP,  denying earlier statements from the All Progressive Congress (APC) that he has decamped to the party. Fani-Kayode said in a  tweet on his verified Twitter handle Femi @realFFK that “Though we have had meetings across party lines and we are in a season of political consultation I have not left the PDP.” Kogi state Governor, Yahaya Bello had in video earlier at a public function announced the defection of former Aviation Minister, Femi Fani Kayode from Though we have had meetings across party lines and we are in a season of political consultation I have not left the PDP. — Femi Fani-Kayode (@realFFK) February 10, 2021  Click Here>>>>>>Anti-kidnap and anti-theft device for tracking and listening<<<<<< 